Proposal Lead
Confidential Company - ,
Date Posted: 2014/05/06 10:59:00
Ref. JB3047842
Job Description
•	Be an active and dynamic participant in the proposal creation/submission process in support of company responses to
Requests for Proposals, Requests for Quotations, Requests for Information, Requests for Pre-Qualification and similar solicitations.
•	Manage and monitor each proposal process to ensure adherence to compliance, quality and timeliness requirements.
•	Ensure all processes are simple, clear, modular and documented in brief Standard Operating Procedures.
•	Keep senior management and executives informed at all stages of the proposal creation/submission process.
•	Participate in the bid/no-bid decision process.
•	Be aware of and fully understand all related Non-Disclosure Agreements and Teaming Agreements.
•	Schedule and assign proposal preparation and submission activities.
•	Identify need for Subject Matter Experts.
•	Work with Business Development Manager to jointly create winning Proposal Themes.
•	Work with Business Development Manager to identify Photograph Requirements.
•	Create Proposal Outline and corresponding Compliance Matrix to ensure content and organization of the proposal strictly follow and address RFP requirements. Update as required.
•	Provide Proposal Outline, Compliance Matrix, Proposal Themes, Photograph Requirements, Basis of Estimate sample, Bill of Quantities sample and RFP documents to Proposal Publisher for creation of hard-copy proposal binders.
•	Provide materials to Business Development Manager for proposal kickoff meeting.
•	Collect, consolidate and QC proposal inputs from Proposal Writer, operational departments, SMEs and pricing personnel.
•	Assist with writing proposal volumes, as necessary.
•	QC written material to ensure compliance, completeness and accuracy.
•	Ensure pricing inputs are supported by adequate Basis of Estimate and Bill of Quantities.
•	Obtain written approval prior to submission of certified cost or pricing data.
•	Provide pricing and technical inputs to Proposal Publisher.
•	Participate in milestone proposal reviews led by Business Development Manager.
•	Provide draft proposal data to milestone review participants.
•	Communicate milestone review comments to the proposal team and retrieve modified proposal inputs for onward submission to Proposal Publisher.
•	Draft and submit solicitation questions to clients.
•	Upon prior approval from senior management, deliver finished proposal products to clients in a professional, compliant and timely manner.
•	Interface with clients in a polite, professional manner and be responsive to ongoing proposal requirements.
•	Participate in post-submission, proposal Hot Wash meetings.
•	Obtain evaluation status on submitted proposals from clients when feedback is delayed.
•	Upon award announcement, request formal debriefings from clients on all submitted proposals.
•	Participate in winning project kickoff meetings.
•	Provide proposal / contract data to kickoff meeting participants.
•	Input proposal status data as required into Business Development databases.
•	Ensure ongoing standardization of proposal volumes.
•	Ensure ongoing improvement of proposal volumes.
•	Ensure practices are in-place to safeguard proprietary information.
•	Ensure Non-Disclosure Agreements are signed by personnel given access to proposal information.
•	Participate in internal and external professional education programs.
•	Perform other related duties as assigned.
Skills
•	Bachelors Degree
•	Minimum 5 years of experience in the field of Proposal Writing
•	Knowledge and experience with the US Government FAR
•	Knowledge and experience writing to commercial and US Government RFPs and tenders
•	Demonstrated ability to identify potential problems with cost, schedule and technical risks of requests for proposals
•	Experience performing Market Research: Conduct, collect and analyze relevant market information and identify possible sources for the proposals through effective market analysis and industry knowledge
•	Experience Defining Customer Requirements: Define the necessary requirements to determine or develop offer evaluation factors that will discriminate between the organizations competition that tie back to the technical requirements included in the solicitation and assist in determining the most appropriate method of proposing
